{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Rom|3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","chapter":3,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":1,"text":"So what advantage does the Jew have? Or what is the benefit of circumcision?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":2,"text":"Considerable in every way. First, they were entrusted with the very words of God.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":3,"text":"What then? If some were unfaithful, will their unfaithfulness nullify God’s faithfulness?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":4,"text":"Absolutely not! Let God be true, even though everyone is a liar, as it is written:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":5,"text":"But if our unrighteousness highlights God’s righteousness, what are we to say? I am using a human argument: Is God unrighteous to inflict wrath?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":6,"text":"Absolutely not! Otherwise, how will God judge the world?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":7,"text":"But if by my lie God’s truth abounds to his glory, why am I also still being judged as a sinner?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":8,"text":"And why not say, just as some people slanderously claim we say, “Let us do what is evil so that good may come”? Their condemnation is deserved!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":9,"text":"What then? Are we any better off? Not at all! For we have already charged that both Jews and Greeks are all under sin,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":10,"text":"as it is written:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":11,"text":"There is no one who understands;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":12,"text":"All have turned away;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":13,"text":"Their throat is an open grave;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":14,"text":"Their mouth is full of cursing and bitterness.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":15,"text":"Their feet are swift to shed blood;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":16,"text":"ruin and wretchedness are in their paths,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":17,"text":"and the path of peace they have not known.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":18,"text":"There is no fear of God before their eyes.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":19,"text":"Now we know that whatever the law says, it speaks to those who are subject to the law, so that every mouth may be shut and the whole world may become subject to God’s judgment.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":20,"text":"For no one will be justified in his sight by the works of the law, because the knowledge of sin comes through the law.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":21,"text":"But now, apart from the law, the righteousness of God has been revealed, attested by the Law and the Prophets.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":22,"text":"The righteousness of God is through faith in Jesus Christ to all who believe, since there is no distinction.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":23,"text":"For all have sinned and fall short of the glory of God;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":24,"text":"they are justified freely by his grace through the redemption that is in Christ Jesus.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":25,"text":"God presented him as the mercy seat by his blood, through faith, to demonstrate his righteousness, because in his restraint God passed over the sins previously committed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":26,"text":"God presented him to demonstrate his righteousness at the present time, so that he would be just and justify the one who has faith in Jesus.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":27,"text":"Where, then, is boasting? It is excluded. By what kind of law? By one of works? No, on the contrary, by a law of faith.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:28","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":28,"text":"For we conclude that a person is justified by faith apart from the works of the law.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:29","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":29,"text":"Or is God the God of Jews only? Is he not the God of Gentiles too? Yes, of Gentiles too,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:30","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":30,"text":"since there is one God who will justify the circumcised by faith and the uncircumcised through faith.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:31","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","bookOrder":44,"chapter":3,"verse":31,"text":"Do we then nullify the law through faith? Absolutely not! On the contrary, we uphold the law.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Rom","chapter":3,"paragraphStarts":[1,5,9,11,12,13,14,15,16,17,18,19,21,27],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Paul Answers an Objection"},{"beforeVerse":9,"text":"The Whole World Guilty before God"},{"beforeVerse":21,"text":"The Righteousness of God through Faith"},{"beforeVerse":27,"text":"Boasting Excluded"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So what advantage does the Jew have? Or what is the benefit of circumcision? "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Considerable in every way. First, they were entrusted "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 4:8","book":"Deu","chapter":4,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 147:19","book":"Psa","chapter":147,"verse":19,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:4","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":4,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" with the very words of God. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 7:38","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":38,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Dt 4:8","book":"Deu","chapter":4,"verse":8},{"label":"Ps 147:19","book":"Psa","chapter":147,"verse":19},{"label":"Rm 9:4","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":4},{"label":"Ac 7:38","book":"Act","chapter":7,"verse":38}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"What then? If some were unfaithful, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 10:16","book":"Rom","chapter":10,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Heb 4:2","book":"Heb","chapter":4,"verse":2,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" will their unfaithfulness nullify God’s faithfulness? "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 10:16","book":"Rom","chapter":10,"verse":16},{"label":"Heb 4:2","book":"Heb","chapter":4,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Absolutely not! "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 20:16","book":"Luk","chapter":20,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 3:31","book":"Rom","chapter":3,"verse":31,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" Let God be true, even though everyone is a liar, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 116:11","book":"Psa","chapter":116,"verse":11,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" as it is written:"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Lk 20:16","book":"Luk","chapter":20,"verse":16},{"label":"Rm 3:31","book":"Rom","chapter":3,"verse":31},{"label":"Ps 116:11","book":"Psa","chapter":116,"verse":11}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But if our unrighteousness highlights "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or shows, or demonstrates"},{"kind":"text","text":" God’s righteousness, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 5:8","book":"Rom","chapter":5,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Co 6:4","book":"2Co","chapter":6,"verse":4,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 2:18","book":"Gal","chapter":2,"verse":18,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" what are we to say? "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 4:1","book":"Rom","chapter":4,"verse":1,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 7:7","book":"Rom","chapter":7,"verse":7,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 8:31","book":"Rom","chapter":8,"verse":31,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:14","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":14,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:30","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":30,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"text","text":" I am using a human argument: "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Lit I speak as a man"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 6:19","book":"Rom","chapter":6,"verse":19,"letter":"i"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 9:8","book":"1Co","chapter":9,"verse":8,"letter":"j"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Co 15:32","book":"1Co","chapter":15,"verse":32,"letter":"k"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 3:15","book":"Gal","chapter":3,"verse":15,"letter":"l"},{"kind":"text","text":" Is God unrighteous to inflict wrath? "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 5:8","book":"Rom","chapter":5,"verse":8},{"label":"2Co 6:4","book":"2Co","chapter":6,"verse":4},{"label":"Gl 2:18","book":"Gal","chapter":2,"verse":18},{"label":"Rm 4:1","book":"Rom","chapter":4,"verse":1},{"label":"Rm 7:7","book":"Rom","chapter":7,"verse":7},{"label":"Rm 8:31","book":"Rom","chapter":8,"verse":31},{"label":"Rm 9:14","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":14},{"label":"Rm 9:30","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":30},{"label":"Rm 6:19","book":"Rom","chapter":6,"verse":19},{"label":"1Co 9:8","book":"1Co","chapter":9,"verse":8},{"label":"1Co 15:32","book":"1Co","chapter":15,"verse":32},{"label":"Gl 3:15","book":"Gal","chapter":3,"verse":15}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or shows, or demonstrates"},{"marker":2,"text":"Lit I speak as a man"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Absolutely not! Otherwise, how will God judge the world? "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 2:16","book":"Rom","chapter":2,"verse":16,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 2:16","book":"Rom","chapter":2,"verse":16}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But if by my lie God’s truth abounds to his glory, why am I also still being judged as a sinner? "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:19","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":19,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 9:19","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":19}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"And why not say, just as some people slanderously claim we say, “Let us do what is evil so that good may come”? "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 6:1","book":"Rom","chapter":6,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" Their condemnation is deserved!"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 6:1","book":"Rom","chapter":6,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"What then? Are we any better off? "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Are we Jews any better than the Gentiles?"},{"kind":"text","text":" Not at all! For we have already charged that both Jews "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 2:1–29","book":"Rom","chapter":2,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" and Greeks "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 1:18–32","book":"Rom","chapter":1,"verse":18,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" are all under sin, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Under sin’s power or dominion"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 3:19","book":"Rom","chapter":3,"verse":19,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 3:23","book":"Rom","chapter":3,"verse":23,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 11:32","book":"Rom","chapter":11,"verse":32,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 3:22","book":"Gal","chapter":3,"verse":22,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 2:1–29","book":"Rom","chapter":2,"verse":1},{"label":"Rm 1:18–32","book":"Rom","chapter":1,"verse":18},{"label":"Rm 3:19","book":"Rom","chapter":3,"verse":19},{"label":"Rm 3:23","book":"Rom","chapter":3,"verse":23},{"label":"Rm 11:32","book":"Rom","chapter":11,"verse":32},{"label":"Gl 3:22","book":"Gal","chapter":3,"verse":22}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Are we Jews any better than the Gentiles?"},{"marker":2,"text":"Under sin’s power or dominion"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"as it is written:"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"There is no one who understands;"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"All have turned away;"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Their throat is an open grave;"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Their mouth is full of cursing and bitterness."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 10:7","book":"Psa","chapter":10,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 10:7","book":"Psa","chapter":10,"verse":7,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 10:7","book":"Psa","chapter":10,"verse":7},{"label":"Ps 10:7","book":"Psa","chapter":10,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Their feet are swift to shed blood;"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"ruin and wretchedness are in their paths,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"and the path of peace they have not known."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 59:7–8","book":"Isa","chapter":59,"verse":7,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 59:7–8","book":"Isa","chapter":59,"verse":7,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 59:7–8","book":"Isa","chapter":59,"verse":7},{"label":"Is 59:7–8","book":"Isa","chapter":59,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"There is no fear of God before their eyes."},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 36:1","book":"Psa","chapter":36,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 36:1","book":"Psa","chapter":36,"verse":1,"letter":"b"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 36:1","book":"Psa","chapter":36,"verse":1},{"label":"Ps 36:1","book":"Psa","chapter":36,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Now we know that whatever the law says, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jn 10:34","book":"Jhn","chapter":10,"verse":34,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" it speaks to those who are subject to the law, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Lit those in the law"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 2:12","book":"Rom","chapter":2,"verse":12,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" so that every mouth may be shut and the whole world may become subject to God’s judgment. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Or become guilty before God, or may be accountable to God"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 2:9","book":"Rom","chapter":2,"verse":9,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jn 10:34","book":"Jhn","chapter":10,"verse":34},{"label":"Rm 2:12","book":"Rom","chapter":2,"verse":12},{"label":"Rm 2:9","book":"Rom","chapter":2,"verse":9}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Lit those in the law"},{"marker":2,"text":"Or become guilty before God, or may be accountable to God"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For no one will be justified "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":3,"text":"Or will be declared righteous, or will be acquitted"},{"kind":"text","text":" in his sight by the works of the law, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ps 143:2","book":"Psa","chapter":143,"verse":2,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 13:39","book":"Act","chapter":13,"verse":39,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 2:16","book":"Gal","chapter":2,"verse":16,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" because the knowledge of sin comes through the law. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 4:15","book":"Rom","chapter":4,"verse":15,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 5:13","book":"Rom","chapter":5,"verse":13,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 5:20","book":"Rom","chapter":5,"verse":20,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 7:7","book":"Rom","chapter":7,"verse":7,"letter":"g"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Ps 143:2","book":"Psa","chapter":143,"verse":2},{"label":"Ac 13:39","book":"Act","chapter":13,"verse":39},{"label":"Gl 2:16","book":"Gal","chapter":2,"verse":16},{"label":"Rm 4:15","book":"Rom","chapter":4,"verse":15},{"label":"Rm 5:13","book":"Rom","chapter":5,"verse":13},{"label":"Rm 5:20","book":"Rom","chapter":5,"verse":20},{"label":"Rm 7:7","book":"Rom","chapter":7,"verse":7}],"footnotes":[{"marker":3,"text":"Or will be declared righteous, or will be acquitted"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"But now, apart from the law, the righteousness of God has been revealed, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 1:17","book":"Rom","chapter":1,"verse":17,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 9:30","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":30,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" attested by the Law and the Prophets. "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"When capitalized, the Law and the Prophets = OT"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 10:43","book":"Act","chapter":10,"verse":43,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 1:2","book":"Rom","chapter":1,"verse":2,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Rm 1:17","book":"Rom","chapter":1,"verse":17},{"label":"Rm 9:30","book":"Rom","chapter":9,"verse":30},{"label":"Ac 10:43","book":"Act","chapter":10,"verse":43},{"label":"Rm 1:2","book":"Rom","chapter":1,"verse":2}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"When capitalized, the Law and the Prophets = OT"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Rom:3:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The righteousness of God is through faith "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Rm 4:5","book":"Rom","chapter":4,"verse":5,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" in Jesus Christ "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":2,"text":"Or through the faithfulness of Jesus Christ"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 3:16","book":"Act","chapter":3,"verse":16,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 2:16","book":"Gal","chapter":2,"verse":16,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gl 2:20","book":"Gal","chapter":2,"verse":20,"letter":"d"},{"kind":